MAC MINI AGENT SERVER

ADR-037 — Session Transcript & Heartbeat Monitoring Framework

Status: DECIDED

Date: March 15, 2026

Phase: 1  |  COMPLETE IMPLEMENTATION (Setup Day Deliverable)

Owner: Sheldon Wheeler

NIST Coverage:  AU-2 · AU-3 · AU-6 · IR-4 · SI-4 · SI-4(2) · SI-4(5)

# 1.  Context and Decision

Agent sessions produce valuable reasoning traces, decisions, code snippets, and learned facts. Without persistent capture and knowledge updates, agents waste tokens re-learning the same content in subsequent sessions. Additionally, agents running nightly jobs or long-running tasks need to emit heartbeats so the operator knows they are alive and progressing.

This ADR formalizes three concurrent capabilities:

- Session Transcript Capture — store user input, agent reasoning, and final output to PostgreSQL and markdown files

- Knowledge Base Auto-Update — extract decisions, code, and facts from transcripts and update agent-owned markdown files (DECISIONS.md, CODE_REFERENCE.md, KNOWLEDGE.md)

- Heartbeat Monitor — concurrent service that polls agent health, service availability (PostgreSQL, Ollama, ChromaDB, Telegram), and emits alerts to Telegram on failure or silence

Decision: Adopt persistent session transcripts with auto-updating knowledge files, and deploy a concurrent health monitor as a separate service running in Docker. Both systems write to PostgreSQL for audit and historical analysis. All logging is structured for NIST compliance and operator visibility.

